subsection.def:
contributing factor (促成因素) means an action, omission, event or
                condition, or a combination of them, that, if eliminated, avoided or absent, would have—(a)reduced the probability of the accident or incident occurring;
                        or(b)mitigated the severity of the consequences of the accident or incident;
                                (L.N. 164 of
                            2024)

crew
                    (機員) includes every person employed or
                engaged in an aircraft in flight on the business of the aircraft;

operator
                    (經營人) in relation to an aircraft means the
                person for the time being having the management of that aircraft;

owner
                    (機主) means, where an aircraft is registered,
                the registered owner;

State of Manufacture (製造國), in relation to an aircraft, means the
                country, territory or place having jurisdiction over the organization responsible
                for the final assembly of—(a)the aircraft; or(b)the engine or propeller of the aircraft; (L.N. 164 of 2024)

subparagraph.content:
it occurs to a civil aircraft registered in Hong Kong in or over a
                        country, territory or place outside Hong Kong that is not a Contracting
                        State;

left at, or sent by post to, the registered office of the company
                        within the meaning of the Companies Ordinance (Cap.
                            622);

paragraph.content:
to take statements from all such persons as he thinks fit and to require any
                such person to make and sign a declaration of the truth of the statement made by
                him;

include particulars of any proposed analysis of facts that may affect the
                    person on whom, or in respect of whom, the notice is
                    served;

is to provide to the Chief Inspector all information relating to the
                    accident or incident concerned in his or her possession or control;
                    and

is to provide to the Chief Inspector all information relating to the
                    accident or incident concerned in his or her possession or control;
                    and

section.def:
non-Hong Kong accident or incident
                (外地意外或事故) means an accident or incident to which
            this Part applies under regulation 3(3);

paragraph.content:
is to provide to the AIA (non-HK) all information relating to the non-Hong
                    Kong accident or incident concerned in his or her possession or control;
                    and

is to provide to the AIA (non-HK) all information relating to the non-Hong
                    Kong accident or incident concerned in his or her possession or control;
                    and

subsection.def:
*commencement
                    date (生效日期) means the commencement
                date of the amending Regulation;

paragraph.content:
anything done before the commencement date under the pre-amended
                    regulations is regarded as having been done under the amended regulations;
                    and

section.def:
*commencement
                date (生效日期) means the date on which the
            amending Regulation comes into operation;
